cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IOT, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a machine learning model for anomaly detection in time series data for Edge Computing in Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IOT. The proposed model is a Squeezed Convolutional Variational AutoEncoder (SCVAE), which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The model uses convolutional layers for feature extraction, making cs.CV a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the reduction in model size and inference times by applying Fire Modules from SqueezeNet, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
